The evolution of Dig Inn to Dig is an ongoing collaboration with the New York City institution, from design and art direction to voice and tone. 

The new identity and personality represent a shift away from youthful minimalism and towards a wholehearted embrace of the richness, color, and integrity of vegetables. 

The brand update and accompanying body of language and visuals speak to the company’s internal culture of hard work and reverence for the vast landscape of the natural world.

Work for Telfar Global
Directed by Santiago Carraquilla
With Vasco Gross, Davi Bonilla, Haolun Liu 
Sound design: Ary Warnaar

TELFAR PUFF REMIX

This is a personal project we’ve been working on since January. Not commissioned by the client, purely self initiated.
A research and development endeavor. A labor of love and great patience! We took a few of the scenes from the ‘Telfar Puff Campaign’ we did late last year - and used Stable Diffusion to bring a new aesthetic to them.
We experimented with many different visual styles and prompts until we found a style we liked. We then made a new edit using all the new animations generated. We printed the entire video at 10 frames per second - a total of 600 frames. And then loosely illustrated over every single one of the frames, with the goal of really collaborating with the AI, re interpreting it, and giving it one last layer of human craft and human creativity. As these new AI tools arrive and develop, we are excited to try them and find our own unique ways of engaging with them.

Made at Art Camp in collaboration with Telfar Global

‘THE FINAL: Argentina vs France’ is an animated short produced by Art Camp. The film celebrates one of the most epic football matches ever played, condensing a game full of goals, emotions, and drama into just one minute. 
Featuring 550 meticulously airbrushed paintings by Chicago-based artist Nicke Apple, each frame is brought to life with breathtaking beauty. 
At the heart of THE FINAL is the fierce battle between two of the greatest football legends of all time: Messi and Mbappé. The film captures the strength and glory of both teams, while also acknowledging the bittersweet reality that, in the end, only one can claim victory.
